<subSubSection id="C31F6509FF84303ECA9DFD30FFF9814B" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBA3682FF84303ECA9DFD30FFF9814B" blockId="2.[136,775,659,770]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B971EA90FF84303ECA9DFD30FF1880E2" bold="true" box="[136,261,659,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B971EA90FF84303ECA9DFD30FEED80E2" bold="true" box="[136,240,659,683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</emphasis>
–
</emphasis>
This species is very common in 
<collectingCountry id="F3127612FF84303EC879FD30FCC580E3" box="[620,728,659,682]" name="Singapore" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Singapore</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3127612FF84303ECA9DFD12FEF18081" box="[136,236,689,712]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, also collected from brackish water. Widespread from 
<collectingCountry id="F3127612FF84303ECADDFD6DFF1180AC" box="[200,268,718,741]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3127612FF84303ECB0EFD6DFF4480AC" box="[283,345,718,741]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Japan</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3127612FF84303ECB91FD6DFFF480AC" box="[388,489,718,741]" name="Australia" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF944B73FF84303ECBEEFD6DFEDC814B" author="Polhemus, J" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" pagination="205 - 230" refId="ref4594" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; D. A. Polhemus, 2000. The genus Mesovelia Mulsant &amp; Rey in New Guinea Heteroptera: Mesoveliidae. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 108 (3 - 4): 205 - 230." type="journal article" year="2000">Polhemus &amp; Polhemus, 2000</bibRefCitation>
; Andersen &amp; Weir, 2004).
</paragraph>
